  "contentPages" : [
    // Page 1
    "To those unfamiliar with Glitch - which is common, given their construction - it may seem strange that Glitch are capable of gaining weight. After all, they're just robots, right?

In truth, Glitch are more advanced than typical machines. Their primary directive is to simulate an evolving civilization, so they mimic many traits of living organisms: breathing air, consuming food and drink, and storing fat.",
    // Page 2
    "The reason for this design goes beyond merely simulating life; artificial fat gives them reserve energy, helping them remain self-sustaining and long-lived.

Their simulated roles are also a factor. Glitch that gain significant weight are often those of noble rank or \"noble oil\".",
    // Page 3
    "From kings and queens to princes, princesses, dukes, and duchesses, nobility are able to enjoy luxuries unavailable to lower classes, and may even unconsciously lean into indulgence.

Because Glitch remain bound by their protocols rather than free will, any fat, pompous nobility they display becomes part of the role their programming forces them to perform."
